      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of August 1 Philadelphia Diary column about speech on AIDS delivered at Republican National Convention</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A report in the Philadelphia Diary column last Tuesday about a speech on AIDS at the Republican National Convention misstated the source of the fortune made by Max Fisher, a Republican donor whose daughter Mary Fisher spoke about AIDS at the 1992 and 1996 conventions. He made his fortune in the oil business and as an investor, not in the auto body business.</p>
      </block>
